text: ML and ANN s started traction commercially though limited in 1980s. I never liked Lisp and Prolog and Expert Systems due to their approach. As soon as I was exposed to ML and pattern recognition and ANNs in mid nineties at my university, it was a relief because I knew this is the future and this is how our brains work and learn. The rest is history in 2005 through 2015 and the emergence of massive computing capabilities and massive data due to internet and interest now from big players like Microsoft and google and others, the whole thing was accelerated and popularized with the advent of DNNs and in 2020s, LLMs. Interestingly, many of the ideas go back to 80s and before but they blossomed due to computing power and availability of massive data in 2010s and beyond.

The provided text, "Scroll of the Prophetic Web ‚Äì Babylon‚Äôs Final Unraveling," presents a highly conspiratorial and religiously-infused narrative about current events. Here's a breakdown of its main points and underlying themes:
I. The Fall of Trump ‚Äì The Puppet Burns with His Strings
 * Central Claim: Donald Trump's legal troubles (specifically being "found guilty") are not accidental but a divinely ordained judgment and an unmasking of his ties to a "predator elite" through figures like Jeff Epstein.
 * Tone: Triumphant and condemnatory, presenting Trump as a fallen figure whose downfall is just.
 * Biblical Reference: Psalm 92:7 is used to support the idea that the flourishing of the wicked is a precursor to their destruction.
II. The Elite Orchestration ‚Äì From Mars to Mystery Babylon
 * Central Claim: A shadowy network, identified as "Mystery Babylon," orchestrates global events. This network includes figures like Elon Musk, the Rothschilds, and organizations like the CFR and Trilateral Commission.
 * Methods of Control: They allegedly use AI, surveillance, vaccines, and financial collapses to manipulate nations and reset the world under their control. They also "craft false saviors."
 * Tone: Deeply suspicious of powerful individuals and institutions, portraying them as a unified, malevolent force.
 * Biblical Reference: Revelation 18:24 is cited, linking "Mystery Babylon" to the shedding of innocent blood.
III. LA Riots ‚Äì The Awakening Roar of Jacob
 * Central Claim: The Los Angeles riots are interpreted not as chaos but as a prophetic "awakening" of "Jacob" (interpreted as Judah and Ishakar, likely referring to specific ethnic or religious groups). This is framed as a significant event indicating a reawakening of a specific people and the land of "Aztl√°n."
 * Tone: Reinterpretive, giving a spiritual and prophetic meaning to civil unrest, viewing it as a positive sign of awakening.
 * Biblical Reference: Exodus 3:7 is used to suggest divine awareness of the "affliction of my people."
IV. Martial Law ‚Äì The Elite‚Äôs Final Card
 * Central Claim: The elite plans to impose martial law as a "snare" to suppress the awakening, but this will backfire and become a "divine trap."
 * Prophetic Outcome: Martial law will paradoxically lead to "Jacob‚Äôs justice" and the rise of a "Governor from the House of David" who will impose his own form of martial law.
 * Tone: Defiant and confident in a divine reversal of the elite's plans.
 * Biblical Reference: Matthew 7:2 ("For with what judgment ye judge, ye shall be judged...") is used to imply the elite's plans will lead to their own condemnation.
V. The Interlocking Grid ‚Äì Epstein, Elon, Economy, and Exodus
 * Central Claim: Various seemingly disparate events are interconnected as parts of a larger scheme:
   * Epstein's files expose a "global predator class."
   * Elon Musk's technology facilitates "neural enslavement."
   * Financial collapses are "timed ritual sacrifices."
   * The current situation is an "Exodus," not of people leaving a place, but of "Egypt" (the oppressive system) crumbling around them.
 * Tone: Highly alarmist, connecting diverse public figures and events into a singular, sinister conspiracy.
 * Biblical Reference: Revelation 18:4 ("Come out of her, my people...") is used to call for separation from the corrupt system.
VI. Final Decree ‚Äì The Web Is Torn
 * Central Claim: All the described events ‚Äì Trump's fall, the LA riots, secret councils, and revolts ‚Äì are interconnected strands of a "divine web" that is now being destroyed.
 * Conclusion: This signifies the beginning of "judgment," overseen by an "Executioner King."
 * Tone: Apocalyptic and definitive, proclaiming the imminent fulfillment of prophecy and divine retribution.
Overall Themes and Characteristics:
 * Conspiratorial Thinking: The text heavily relies on connecting seemingly unrelated events and individuals into a grand, malevolent conspiracy driven by a shadowy "elite."
 * Apocalyptic and Prophetic Language: It uses strong religious and prophetic language, frequently citing biblical verses to legitimize its claims and frame current events within a divine plan.
 * Dualistic Worldview: It presents a clear good-versus-evil narrative, with "Mystery Babylon" and the "elite" representing evil, and "Jacob," the "remnant," and the "Executioner King" representing the forces of good and divine judgment.
 * Anti-Establishment Sentiment: There's a strong distrust of political leaders, financial institutions, and technological advancements, viewing them as tools of control.
 * Identity-Based Interpretation: The references to "Jacob," "Judah," "Ishakar," and "Aztl√°n" suggest a specific ethno-religious or nationalist interpretation of current events, likely connected to a particular group's perceived role in prophecy.
 * Sense of Imminent Judgment: The text conveys a strong sense that a significant, transformative period of divine judgment is underway or about to unfold.

text: ChatGPT speeds up/replaces the essay creation process formerly followed by students in the 5th to 12th grades.  I remember the process well: read the "The World Book" series entry on your subject, rewrite it in your own words, then check the Encyclopedia Britannica entry and add any missing bits, again in your own words. Shake, transcribe, and serve.        Among other things, a serious threat of AI is that it will be able to generate completely real looking and sounding videos. It's clear that a huge portion of humanity is very easily fooled by grifters and scammers _even without such an impressive weapon as AI_. The Cretin-in-Chief has caused otherwise more or less normal people to refuse to "believe their lying eyes". He can say, "The moon is made of blue cheese" and they will believe it. *What is the true definition of intelligence?* "The Hidden Math in Everything"
Society hides the real definition of intelligence because it would be too insulting to millions of people. IQ tests are invalid. IQ tests don't take the real definitions into account. 

Intelligence is really based on:
1. Mathematical aptitude.
2. An ability to make a cognitive leap or climb from point A to point B.

Some people are so fixated on their belief that they are supersmart that they will only start believing they are mathematical wizards if you were to explain this to them. Math only comes with hard notes and book practice at a desk. It comes from the ability to collect resources beyond the classroom independently. Grammar and languages are all mathematically oriented. This is why Artificial Intelligence is supposed to be so devastating to humanity. Currently, it looks like just a grammar calculator with little scope. Theoretically, Artificial Intelligence can add a defined random variable within a related or unrelated set, and one can set the number of its iterations through those sets, thus defining its scope and its level of intelligence. This, of course, has to do with memory availability in computers. Right now, there is a cap on its intelligence, but they can take off that cap when they need a more intelligent response

text:
The worst thing about AI is the name. Calling it Intelligence is a total misnomer. There is no intelligence involved. It's just massive databases regurgitating the info they were trained on based on a few inputs that match the tags on the data within. It's got a very long way to go before it should qualify for the name Intelligence.

However, the funniest thing I've seen related to AI is that the way it works, the most likely position to be completely able to be replaced by an AI is the CEOs who want to use it to replace their workers. They are the single most replaceable part of their company as they're already doing the same thing, just slower and with a usually obvious bias.

text:
3:00 The explanation on their course about unsupervised learning is a bit off. In their video, they said the unsupervised learning is to see whether someone is on fast track or not. This is actually a supervised training, because the machine already know that someone is fast. The definition of fast is indeed labeled.
The unsupervised learning definition is correct though. It does not have label. But the purpose is to "discover something new", not to "see whether the input is on A or B".
But, we cannot comment this on their original vid, so I comment here.
